Constructor Detail

Phoneme

public Phoneme(java.lang.String name,
               int inherentDuration,
               int minimalDuration,
               java.lang.String phonology,
               int sonority,
               java.lang.String example)
Create a new Phoneme object, with the settings specified. name is the phonetic symbol for this segment. inherentDuration and minimalDuration are values for the Klatt rules of duration specification. phonology is a String consisting of 9 characters, each of them a + or a - character, which have the following meanings (in this order): vowel, syllabic, voiced, sonorant, liquid, nasal, glide, plosive, and pause. E.g., the string "--++-+---" describes a nasal consonant, i.e. voiced, sonorant, and nasal. example is a free text string giving a pronounciation example of the segment, which may be the empty string.
